data.content:
noun
plural -outs
[noncount] :the condition of someone who has become very physically and emotionally tired after doing a difficult job for a long time
Teaching can be very stressful, and many teachers eventually suffer/experience burnout.
the burnout rate among teachers
[count] :a person who suffers burnout
a novel about academic burnouts - see also burned out burn out 4 at 1burn
[noncount] :the time when a jet or rocket engine stops working because there is no more fuel available
